Assuming that the parameter is not null and that it contains at least one character, the function isPalindrome can be written as follows:

```
public static boolean isPalindrome(String str) {
    if (str == null || str.isEmpty()) {
        return false;
    }

    char[] chars = str.toCharArray();
    for (int i = 0, j = chars.length - 1; i < j; i++, j--) {
        if (chars[i] != chars[j]) {
            return false;
        }
    }
    return true;
}

